edit.body: AES is suggested as it is more efficient. However it's not a one way hash function. To implement it using AES, you can do something like encrypt the input (x1, x2) using AES in cbc mode, where the key some public info like the ID of the plot, and then truncate to the desired y size (like 40 bits). The truncation at the end, makes it behave like a one way function. Given y (the truncated ciphertext), you can't decrypt, even knowing the AES key, which is public, since AES blocks are 128 bits
